  "text": "The three core Kafka Streams architecture abstractions are: (1) **Topology class** (github.com/sg-evals/kafka--0753c489/streams/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/streams/Topology.java): A public class that represents a logical ProcessorTopology, a graph of sources, processors, and sinks that defines the DAG of processing nodes. It provides methods to construct the computation graph. (2) **StreamsBuilder class** (github.com/sg-evals/kafka--0753c489/streams/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/streams/StreamsBuilder.java): A public class that implements the high-level Kafka Streams DSL for building topologies. It provides a convenient API for constructing stream processing applications with operators like stream(), table(), and transformations, ultimately building a Topology object. (3) **KafkaStreams class** (github.com/sg-evals/kafka--0753c489/streams/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/streams/KafkaStreams.java): A public class that implements AutoCloseable and serves as the runtime client that executes a topology. It coordinates multiple stream processing threads, manages consumer/producer instances, handles rebalancing and fault tolerance, and provides the operational interface for starting, stopping, and monitoring stream processing applications."
}

